Using the Topology Util, you can change it at runtime too e.g if you wanted to make the nodes with ID 1, 2 and 3 #blue, you could do the following.

mainTopology.util.isReady().then(function(response)  );



As long as you have access to the topology.util object, you can control the colors as well as appearance of nodes from anywhere within your UI application at any point.

A node icon can be set at runtime. For instance, if we want to change the icon of a router to brick wall because we like bricks, we can do the following:

