 Interaction Configurable Properties

In various Topologies and use cases, there may be different needs calling for disabling certain user interaction events.
The current list of optional interaction properties within the Topology are as follows bellow. These properties are all false by 
default. In order to set them pass them as a value within your TOPO_PROPs object.

disableZoom: true, // Prevent zoom from occurring within the Topology. Allows you to keep at a set scale.
disableNodeDrag: true, // Prevent nodes from being dragged by the user so reposition is not possible.
disableCanvasDragH: true, // Prevent the Topology View from moving on the horizontal axis.
disableCanvasDragH: true, // Prevent the Topology View from moving on the vertical axis.
